This week on the @blackfolx podcast, BKG (@brandonkgood ) welcomes actor and writer Clark Moore (@mrclarkmoore ). In this clip they also discuss racism in the work place.
For the full episode link in stories!

node.text: Hollywood producers let’s start treating crew like real people. These stories make me sick to my stomach when I think about my friends putting their lives  and health at risk in order to make film and TV. Too often in this industry people are made to feel replaceable and lucky to be working.  It HAS to stop especially with COVID protocols being as they are. All actors that  I know and work with I encourage you to speak up. Follow @ia_stories and speak up for your crew. #iasolidarity

Anonymous, submit via DM. linktr.ee/IAStories'.

Photo by Tom Ellis on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'row. However, it's worse for other crews within the show. Our lighting department hasn't hasn't had a day off off in 30 days. Our construction works day/ nights 6 days a week for the last 6 months. Our painters are currently 6 months straight without a day off.'.

Photo by Tom Ellis on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'was on my 2 hour drive home at 5am after an overnight. I woke up rolling down the right shoulder of the freeway around 10 mph, my foot off the gas and brake, hitting the little speed bump turtles on the lane edge Bump.... bump.... bump..." going Last remember was in the far left lane. have no idea how long I had been out.'.

Photo by Tom Ellis on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'and witnessed a rigger slip and fall three stories off of a set facade, through an overhang, and onto a pile of cable. Its a miracle the cable was there because if it hadn't softened his landing he could have died. They stopped for maybe five minutes to check on him, loaded him up in an ambulance then just went right back to another 16+ hr shooting day like nothing had happened. It was shocking to witness firsthand how taking chortoute'.

Photo by Tom Ellis on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'me. When COVID hit and forced me to stop working became pregnant and had a healthy baby I was literally going from show to show, averaging 68-75+ hours week... not including drive time of course. no sleep, no time to eat healthy, exercise, my stress level was always through the roof and my mental health was suffering. missed countless family get togethers and events to support my spouse.'.

Photo by Tom Ellis on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ia_stories Just did 19 hours, when I asked the AD if could leave because I had been there for too many hours she said "You're a PA 1st to come in last to leave, get used to it" This is depressing...'.
